This is a simple proof-of-concept program that can be used to
communicate covertly  over TCP/IP.


Other files you might look into:
================================

`AUTHORS' - Contributing authors to this program
`README'  - This file
`COPYING' -	Copying conditions
`INSTALL' -	General compilation and installation rules


Some issues to consider when using this program:
================================================

This application makes use of BSD-style TCP/IP headers, which should be
included in any up-to-date Linux distribution. This is done in order to
achieve maximum portability between Linux, *BSD, and Max OS X systems.
